com.camerontec.util.functional

Class CollectionFunctions

  • java.lang.Object
    • com.camerontec.util.functional.CollectionFunctions

  • public final class CollectionFunctions
extends Object
    Suite of common functions performed on standard Java collections framework members.

    Note that this is not intended to be anything like a complete suite for functional Java, rather to provide some useful common functional operations over standard Java collections (which 3rd party functional libraries typically do not do). For more comprehensive functional treatment please consult the functional Java programming library of your choice.

    Note: Some methods below do not create any intermediate objects. While this is true of the methods themselves, no such guarantee is given for the underlying JVM libraries. For example, intermediate objects are often created when iterating over collections and that is a common technique used by most methods. As always, if intermediate object creation is a potential issue then test thoroughly before making any assumptions about the methods in this class.

    • Method Detail

      • filter

        public static <A,B extends Collection<A>> B filter(Iterable<A> collection,
                                                   UnaryPredicate<A> predicate,
                                                   B result)
        Filter a collection based on the evaluation of the specified predicate on each element in the collection.

        Recall also that a java.util.Map is not a java.util.Collection, so this method is inappropriate for filtering maps. Use filter(java.util.Map, UnaryPredicate) instead.

        Type Parameters:
        A - The input collection element type.
        B - The resultant collection type.
        Parameters:
        collection - The source collection. Not modified by this method.
        predicate - The element predicate. Called once per element in the source collection. When it evaluates to true the element is retained in the resultant collection, otherwise it is discarded.
        result - The resultant collection. Must not be null.
        Returns:
        The resultant collection.

      • filter

        public static <K,V> Map<K,V> filter(Map<K,V> map,
                                    UnaryPredicate<K> predicate)
        Filter a map based on the evaluation of the specified predicate on the key of each entry in the map.

        This method creates and returns a new java.util.Map object containing the filter results. Iteration order (if defined) over the source map is maintained in the resultant map. In addition, another intermediate object is created in the process of filtering the map's key set.

        Type Parameters:
        K - The key type.
        V - The value type.
        Parameters:
        map - The source map. Not modified by this method.
        predicate - The element predicate. Called once per entry key in the source map. When it evaluates to true the entry is retained in the resultant map, otherwise it is discarded.
        Returns:
        The resultant map.

        public static <A,B> B foldRight(List<A> list,
                                UnaryFunction<B,UnaryFunction<A,B>> function,

        Perform a fold right reduction across the specified list.

        This method is similar to foldLeft(java.util.List, UnaryFunction, Object), except that the list is traversed in reverse order.
